1. Setup Github repository for the project 
2. Use Terraform to provision EC2 instance in AWS
    a. t2.micro
    b. Enable SSH access to it (Security Group)
    c. Use your Public SSH key for accessing
    b. Use elastic IP and attach it to EC2 instance
3. Use Terraform to provision RDS instance in AWS
    a. t2.micro
    b. MySQL
    c. Access from EC2 instance (Security Group)
4. Use Ansible to setup a Wordpress application using Docker on EC2 instance
    a. Install Docker
    b. Start Wordpress Container
    c. Configure it to use below-mentioned AWS RDS for MySQL
5. Use Github personal repository to store all the codebase of the project 
6. Setup Github Actions as CI/CD for pipeline to provision above mentioned infrastructure
